caption: A perfect sandwich shop! Very friendly staff!
Great place to eat
Great place for a sandwich and a brownie (they're awesome!). The Black and Blue is my favorite!

The food is great, dont get me wrong, but can never eat here because these folks are always closing early! I've only managed to eat here twice since I've discovered the place since they always close around noon every time I try to stop in.
I never tried a better sandwich, rueben and beer cheese soup is to kill for.
They make great sandwiches
Always great best Beer cheese soup I’ve had
Very good Jerk Chicken and awesome customer service
LOVED The Hot Brown! Absolutely lovely people and great service.
Fred is the man! Everyone is very friendly and the sandwiches are amazing. Can’t wait to go back for a Monte Cristo!
So delicious.  The pickles taste homemade and heavenly.  The bread is perfect.  Everything is delicious.  Do youself a favor and go here.

If their other sandwiches are as good as the Black and Bleu, then 5 stars all around!  The meat was tender and flavor was good. Bread tastes fresh. Just moved here and will definitely be back to try the other sandwiches!
R.I.P Daniel!! Sandwich shop need to be open to help pay medical bills!!
Long wait, but the food is definitely worth it. Highly recommend the brownies.
Loved the corn beef it was juicy and delicious
Good sandwiches but they always seem to be out of something.
First time and loved it!

Great sandwiches, even better brownies. We had the Beastie boy and Beastie girl sandwiches. They were good, the boy (very different, with meat, cheese and corn) better than the girl which was a little generic (although, filled with great meat). The brownies are amazing and gooey, so don't miss them.
Great sandwiches and subs. Very friendly staff.
Small but well maintained, neat and clean. Services was nice, polite staff members. Efficient work done by whole team.
Best sandwiches and people
Great sandwich, great service!
Rae's is ALWAYS delicious!
Best place downtown to get a 🥪!
The foods great and the service is even better.

Visiting some friends from out of town. We stopped here on our way back to the airport. Well worth the visit. Black and Bleu was amazing, tender beef and great flavors. Smoked turkey and pepper jack was great as well. Bread was on point. …
I'm in love with their Reuben sandwich and fast service!
Great service and food.
Rae's catered an event I hosted and everyone loved it! They put together a great looking and great tasting tray of sandwiches. I highly recommend Rae's for any lunch meeting you need to cater!
I love affordable delis and this one is great. I will be back again for the hot pastrami!
A favorite downtown lunch spot. The Monte Cristo is amazing and yes you want the pickle.
Make sure you get the pickle with your sandwich.
Always good. Every sandwich and brownie is delicious.
Shrimp Po Boy

A great place to grab lunch. The staff was extremely nice and everything was fresh. I really enjoyed the atmosphere of the place. Your looking at around $10-15 bucks for a sandwich with chips and drink so not bad for Nashville. Definitely …

The shrimp po boy was awesome. The remoulade and bread were both excellent. Service was excellent and for the quality of the food, the price wasn't bad either. I'd recommend getting there by 11:15 AM for lunch if you want to avoid a wait in line.

Its OK here. Sandwiches are good, but personally I dont see what all the fuss is about.  It's just an OK Sandwich shop where you get shouted at if you dont order quick enough. I get the quirkiness of that, but still just average for me.
This was my favourite lunch while working in Downtown Nashville.  The service is friendly and the Monte Cristo is especially delicious!

This place is small and can be a little crowded, but there's a reason for that.  The food is great.  There's a large selection of sandwiches on the menu as well as a few soup and pasta options and daily specials.   My personal favorite is the turkey pot roast melt, but really you can't go wrong with anything on the menu.

Even though there is only 1 vegetarian option on the menu, I highly recommend it! If you like artichokes and cheese you will be just as hooked as I am! So so delicious. The best part of going to this incredibly good little hole in the wall sandwich shop is they make you feel like part of the family 😍 Get into it! ♥️
Great people, wonderful sandwiches!
Great place for lunch.  Busy most days. The staff is very patient and great at getting out during rushes.

This is one of my favorite places to grab a bite while on my lunch break. I love the black and blue sandwich. It is always SO delicious. The line moves pretty quickly and the employees are very friendly! I recommend this place all the time to people traveling and if you're a local, you HAVE to go.
Great food. Great atmosphere
Only open a few hours a day to keep the doctor away... nice environment. I had the Hot Brown. Good sandwich spot for the family
I love them. Their food is amazing and they are the sweetest.
Delicious Sandwiches with Lots of varieties. Staff was Good to me and Service was fantastic. I love being here and always have great experience eating here.
They have the best black and blue sandwhich.

Super tasty sandwiches (we got the Reuben and Monte Cristo). Great prices. We didn't wait long but the line was to the door the whole time we ate. The staff was friendly and works really well together!
Hand made, fresh, great service, always consistent!
The Reuben was fair. Friendly staff that was fast and efficient although it was crowded. Not sure if I would return.
Great tasting sandwiches here. Lunch line is long here. Get here early.
Really good, fresh sandwiches.  I don't know how they do it. Orders placed verbally and he remembers them all! Can be a little crowded.
Great sandwiches
Rae's is a lunch staple. I'm always glad I stopped in and picked up a Black and Bleu.
Love this place and always try to visit for lunch when in Nashville.
Love this place, the staff, and their food!
Mmm, yummy sandwiches!

Daniel, Fred and their family are so kind. They are not just a sandwich shop, they are food artists. Their brownies are the best in the southwest. Even better than the great food and service, they treat people with respect and kindness. I will drive across the state to eat there again.
Excellent food and friendly staff. Very fast services!
The hot sandwiches are the best.

Traveling through on business and I thought I’d stop here since it was packed. I see why it was packed! They make sandwiches the way they should be made.....great bread! I don’t normally even eat sandwiches anymore but I’m glad I stopped here today. Oh and also EXCELLENT customer service which makes it an even better choose.
We ordered the Beastie Boy and Beastie Girl.  We both loved them, they were super tasty.  Highly recommend!
My first visit.. I will be back.  My sandwich  The Cuban, was Amazing, great staff, wonderful atmosphere.
Great sandwiches, best around downtown.
It's good
This place rules. Not going to find a better sandwich shop in the downtown area.
Absolutely LOVE this place! Great food, friendly service, all in downtown Nashville. Dan and Kim know what they're doing and they do it well! Also, congrats on the new grandbaby!
Food food and friendly AF...

The food may be great, but I never got to try it.  Arriving at 11:00 for lunch as the second person there I stood in an unmoving and unserviced line for 45 minutes ignored by all the folks (at least five) there and then left.  Very disappointed.
I had the Beasty Girl sandwich.  French bread was crisp and beef was tender.  Very delicious!
Always great customer service there. Orders are promptly prepared. They make every customer feel welcomed.
Customer service was amazing. Large portions. Great desserts. I got the Dixie chicken salad and it was good but a tad bit bland.
Great food!
Great sandwichs and employees.
Best sandwiches in Downtown Nashville. Try the beasties girl, great tasting sandwich.
Shrimp po boy on Tuesday is my favorite!

Very friendly and fast service some of the best fresh made sandwitches and daily soups. I had the chicken salad and,it was one of the best i have had . I would defiantly recommend it . one of down town Nashville's hidden food gems .
One of the best sandwich places downtown. Great selection of hot sauce too 👍👍🔥
So so tuna sandwich
Awesome place for a tasty sandwich.
Really great lunch spot! Friendly service, delicious food. There's usually a line, but it moves quickly. Daily soup and sandwich specials.

Awesome customer service with southern charm. Soups and sandwiches all with a flair that makes them delicious as well as unique. One of my favorites when I want something a little different.  Small seating area that is clean, and cosy.
Oh my goodness Wowza!!!! Best sandwich in the universe..will definitely be back again!!!
They have the freshest bread and best "put together" sandwiches in town. Wait time was a little long around noon but the atmosphere was great!
If you work in downtown Nashvile, you know RAE's.  5 stars all the way!
Hell Yeah!!!
Fair service / fair food / fair atmosphere. I would go back.
Great little sandwich shop where the food is good and the people are personable.
Delicious sandwiches
AMAZING!
Great service! The best Monte Cristo!
The best sandwiches in downtown Nashville. Consistent taste and quality. Great customer service.
Gotta have the Monte Cristo
Everyone is sincerely nice and kind, the food is great and the brownies are the BEST ever!!
Best sandwiches you will ever have. The wicked chicken is my personal favorite... Its on the spicier side. The shrimp poboy special on Tues is another fav
Wonderful launch spot.  Great selection, good prices.  Come on Friday for the crab cake sandwich.
You haven't had a sandwich 'til you've had Rae's
Great sandwich great price!
Excellent service salads, and sandwiches. I loved the Ruben and chefs salad.
The Hot Brown is a must.  Fred behind the counter is a delight to do business with.  Will be back.

What else can you say but...... THE BEST! I love everything about Rae's. The soups, sandwiches, sides, and desserts are all phenomenal. To top it off, everyone that works there is super friendly and all around great people.
Great food and great people.

Local favorite for a reason! We love the sandwiches and the sweet treats. The brownies are unbelievably and highly suggest you try some soup. They have a few new menu items I am looking forward to catching them in stock!

Great sandwiches, soup, sides, salads and more.  They treat you like friends and fix whatever you want the way you like it. Don't be late on Thursday or the line will be out the door. Their beer cheese soup (and the shrimp bisque on Tuesday) are fantastic!
Best sandwiches in town! Great staff, friendly atmosphere, good eats. Put me down for a Reuben any time.

Went to Rae's for the first time today. Tried their special of the day "Jerk Chicken" . I told the guy(the older white man) that was taking my order that it was my first time visiting . I ordered my sandwich and told him the bread i wanted, …
Angus Po' Boy. Absolutely the best sandwich I've ever had. I may have to eat here every day until the end of time

It was good. The people at Rae's know you if you're a regular, and treat you kindly if you're not. I got a angus beef and mushroom with cheese sauce sub, and expected more cheese sauce than it had. The double chocolate brownie was to die for, really rich and yummy.
Good sandwiches, friendly staff, finding parking downtown for lunch... disaster
Excellent sandwiches, reasonable prices.
Such a great place!
Great place for lunch
Great eats with a couple sides of sarcastic service & customers. Not the best social environment. But as far as the food: 4 out of 5 stars.
A personal touch to everyday lunch, it's a quick, cheap, and delicious lunch options in chain filled downtown Nashville.
Good food, but the BEST brownies in the world. I don't think they have actually won that award, but  I think they deserve it.

Went to Rae's on a whim, turned out to be an amazing experience. The owner knew several of the customers in line by name, pretty awesome. The sandwiches were amazing and the price did not break the bank. All in all if you're craving a great bite and are tired of Subway and it's ilk give Rae's a try.
Best sandwich shop in Nashville!

I used to eat Subway and then Quizno's. One day I ate lunch at Rae's and I was sold and I never looked back. All of their sandwiches are unique and very tasty. Their red beans and rice is the best in town. Get there early for lunch or you …
I was in Nashville for a week and ate here at least 3 times. Fred hooked me up and everyone there is great. The food is delicious, and the prices are fair. Skip Subway and Jimmy John's, go to Rae's!

The sandwiches are not your ordinary sub shop sandwiches. They have a unique twist on flavors and specialties. The Hot Brown and the Monte Cristo are my favorites. Do you like brownies? Get one; or be like most of the corporate offices …

Best place to grab a hot sandwich in town. It's a bit of a hike from 2nd Ave but totally worth it. Make sure to try their Reuben and the Wicked Chicken. They've also got a collection of well over fifty different kinds of hot sauces to choose from.

By far my favorite place to go for lunch downtown, and I go at least once a week. The Wicked Chicken is my regular order (spicy with chipotle peppers), which after going in consistently the staff knows! They know their regulars (and their …
Ordered the Monte Cristo.  Bread was fresh and the cheese sauce was delicious.  They were so friendly that I'd go back even if I didn't like the food!  You will not be disappointed.

Best deli experience in downtown Nashville.  Sandwiches and salads are top-notch, although the one soup I had was merely passable.  Excellent quality ingredients, and if it's your thing, Rae carries a giant selection of obscure hot sauces. …
I wished that they would open the doors on time and be conscientious of others' time.
